  "text": "Moreover, following Direction 1, complex reality needs to be understood from several perspectives. It is critical to define and become aware of our own perspective not only for the development of one's own perspective but for the understanding and development of other perspectives. Pluralism can be enhanced as future studies more actively seize opportunities for theorising at the intersection, that is, borrowing, extending and transforming theories from other fields [CITATION_1] . In this regard, metaphors can also be powerful, as they provide fresh insights (Tsoukas, 1991) .",
